  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Start by frying your chicken thighs on a medium heat. Fry them until they're cooked through and brown on each side. Set aside for later."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Thinly slice the chilli and garlic. Add some more olive oil into the now empty pan and add the rosemary, chilli, and tomatoes. Give everything a good stir to allow for the tomatoes to soften slightly."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Orzo time! Add your orzo to the pan followed by your chicken stock, passata and single cream. Keep stirring until the orzo has cooked through and the pasta is creamy, adding a splash of water if needed. Add salt and pepper. Tear up your basil, add stir through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now it’s ready to serve - Slice up your chicken thighs. Share the orzo between bowls and top with chicken. Grate some Parmesan over the top, and tuck in."
